        print("4. üîç Live Comparison - Real-time before/after")
        print("5. üöÄ Processing Buttons - Apply and save results")
        
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"‚ùå Demo failed: {e}")

def print_interface_help():
    """Print detailed help for the interface"""
    print("""
üéØ MTG Selective Enhancement Interface - Complete Guide

üìã INTERFACE SECTIONS:

1. üéØ SELECTIVE AREA TOOL
   ‚Ä¢ Choose from 5 card type presets
   ‚Ä¢ Each preset selects 4 areas: art, text, border, name
   ‚Ä¢ Selecting a preset replaces all current selections
   
2. üìä SELECTION DISPLAY  
   ‚Ä¢ Shows all 4 selected areas with colored overlays
   ‚Ä¢ Red: Art area, Green: Text area, Blue: Border area, Yellow: Name area
   ‚Ä¢ Displays percentage coverage for each area

3. ‚öôÔ∏è IMAGE PROCESSING SLIDERS
   ‚Ä¢ Real-time adjustment of enhancement settings
   ‚Ä¢ Art Settings: Optimized for artwork enhancement
   ‚Ä¢ Text Settings: Optimized for text readability
   ‚Ä¢ All changes update the live preview automatically

4. üîç LIVE COMPARISON
   ‚Ä¢ Side-by-side original vs enhanced preview
   ‚Ä¢ Updates automatically when sliders change
   ‚Ä¢ Shows current settings and statistics

5. üöÄ PROCESSING BUTTONS
   ‚Ä¢ Apply Enhancement: Process with current settings
   ‚Ä¢ Save Result: Save enhanced image
   ‚Ä¢ Save Comparison: Save side-by-side comparison

üéÆ WORKFLOW:
1. Choose card type preset (normal, art, full art, planes1, planes2)
2. Adjust enhancement sliders while watching live preview
3. Click "Apply Enhancement" when satisfied
4. Save your results

üìã PRESETS:
‚Ä¢ normal: Standard MTG card layout
‚Ä¢ art: Larger art area for art-focused cards  
‚Ä¢ full art: Full art cards with minimal text
‚Ä¢ planes1: Planeswalker layout type 1 (coordinates TBD)
‚Ä¢ planes2: Planeswalker layout type 2 (coordinates TBD)
""")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("üéØ MTG Interface Module Part 2 Loaded!")
    print("Use: create_enhanced_selective_interface(enhancer) for full interface")
    print("Or run: quick_enhancement_demo() for a quick demo")
